Andrea L. Thompson, a former military officer from South Dakota, has been nominated to be the Under Secretary of State for Arms Control and International Security. She currently serves as a Special Advisor in the Office of Policy Planning at the Department of State. Thompson has over 25 years of military service in the U.S. Army, including deployments to Afghanistan, Iraq, and Bosnia. She has also held positions such as Deputy Assistant to the President and National Security Advisor to the Vice President at the White House, National Security Advisor to the House Homeland Security Committee, and Executive Officer to the Under Secretary of the Army. Thompson has a background in journalism and Spanish, with degrees from the University of South Dakota, Long Island University, and the National Defense University.